title: For Sale/Trade:  U.S. Army Colt M1911A1 1943
postcontent:
I have for sale a very nice original U.S. Army M1911A1 Colt 45. The serial number establishes this service pistol was manufactured by Colt in 1943 for the U.S. Military. All markings are consistent with this being an original complete piece. G.H.D ordinance mark represent Brig. General Guy H. Drewry, Springfield Ordinance District, Army inspector of ordinance, June 17, 1942 to July 15, 1945. P stamp in front of rear sights matches P on lower receiver next to magazine release as well as P on barrel. G stamp on lower receiver in front of hammer marks government production. All parts original to this pistol. Pistol is fully operational and represents an era of proud U.S. History. Normal wear for a pistol 70+ years old and in excellent condition. I have no history related to the actual service of this weapon but certainly spanned the period of pacific and European service in World War II, Korea, and Vietnam. This weapon had a very proud service to our nation. Sale includes green canvas duel magazine pouch marked 1943 on back as well as a leather duel magazine pouch marked U.S. Milwaukee Saddlery Co 1946. Two magazines are included but not sure they are authentic to the production era of the pistol. 

Asking $2200

Shoots 80 grains bullets in one little hole- less than one-quarter MOA. Less than 500 rounds down barrel. Sale includes:

1. BAT VR  repeater action with integral picatinny scope mounting rail and integral recoil lug. RBRP. Fluted Bolt.
2. Krieger Stainless Steel #5 contour 1-10 twist flutted barrel 24 inches long threaded for suppressor or muzzle brake.
3. Chambering in 6mm BR no-turn neck for blue box Lapua (.271 nk) .080 FB

8. Hard case for shipping.
9. Load data included in shipping box for buyer.
10. Screw on thread protector for muzzle threads.

If buyer does not want left-handed stock OR THE H-S PRECISION RIGHT HANDED STOCK, I would consider selling just the barreled action, but I prefer to sell as package.
